OOC: And so the first bot finds where the Rogues hang out.  Don't 
expect life to be easy; Rogue Star's defenses and sensors are fully 
operational and a single transformer has no hope in hell of breaking 
or sneaking through.

Torin/Phoenix::

Flat-out bored, Torin watches the screens.  Without replacement 
parts, the engines cannot be brought online.  The jack-of-all-trades 
bot feels a wave of frustration, knowing that Rogue Star has lost its 
most crucial advantage - maneuverability - while leaving most of its 
other systems functional like a taunt.

Then the scanners pick up a lone Predacon, making a beeline for the 
downed ship.  Torin blinks.  How could they have penetrated the 
Rogues' cloaking technology so easily?  Concerned, he monitors the 
interloper's approach, sending a coded alert to Gatara.

-----

Phoenix collapses to the floor in despair at her sitiuation.  If only 
she could get the door open!  But all her efforts are in vain; 
nothing she can think of would budge the portal other than firing her 
incendiary rockets at it - and she lacks ammunition for her weapons.

Burying her head in her arms, the prisoner cries herself to sleep.
